A Tinubu Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos has ordered a musician, Adeyemi Fashola, popularly known as Naira Marley to appear in court for arraignment for alleged car theft on January 14, 2020 The Magistrate, Mr Tajudeen Elias warned Marley that a bench warrant would be issued for his arrest if he failed to appear. Tajudeen made the order in the trial of three other defendants including two of Marley’s brothers. ALSO READ: Court orders arrest, arraignment of Naira Marley over alleged car, iPhone theft Poor vision in children increasing concern —Experts Experts name best chewing stick for healthy teeth Pregnancy possible soon after giving birth —Experts Only 5% of health facilities cover tuberculosis —Dr Osakwe The defendants, Idris Fashola, 18; Babatunde Fashola, 24; and Kunle Obere, 22, are facing a four-count charge bordering on conspiracy, stealing, assault and obstructing the arrest of Naira Marley. They were arraigned on December 16, but Marley was absent. The court granted the three defendants N500,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. MR Elias ordered the Investigative Police Officer (IPO) to produce Marley before the court today (December 21), when the case would be listed for further hearing. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
